properties.headline: Marine Weather Statement issued January 23 at 12:12AM CST by NWS Corpus Christi TX
properties.description:
Moist onshore flow over the relatively cooler shelf waters will
lead to patchy sea fog through mid morning Thursday. Visibilities
will generally range from 2 to 4 nautical miles, with patchy
dense fog of 1 nautical mile or less at times in bays and
nearshore waters.

Mariners over the Bay Waters and over the Nearshore Coastal
Waters within 20 nautical miles offshore are urged to prepare for
rapidly changing visibilities.
